attempts.equation: a = params[0]*x + params[1]*x^2 + params[2]*x^3 + params[3]*x^4 + params[4]*x^5 + params[5]*x^6 + params[6]*x^7 + params[7]*x^8 + params[8]*x^9 + params[9]*v
attempts.comment: Nonlinear harmonic oscillator modeled as 9th-degree polynomial in position x plus linear velocity damping. The system exhibits highly nonlinear position-dependent damping that requires many more parameters to capture accurately. With 10 parameters, the minimum achievable MSE is approximately 1.6e-3, far from the target 1e-7. Analysis showed that at vâ‰ˆ0, a degree-9 polynomial in x achieves MSE~1.2e-7, but the complex velocity-dependent damping term requires additional parameters to model.
